#!F-adobe-helvetica-medium-r-normal--18*
#!N 
#!CSeaGreen #!N  #!Rtadts Adding Input 
Tabs to Tool Icons #!N #!EC #!N #!N Tools such as 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Compute #!EF ,  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Options #!EF , and  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Switch 
#!EF , among others, can have a variable number of inputs. 
If you need more tabs than the number shown by a 
default icon, you can increase the number: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   
#!N #!N #!I30 #!N 1. Select the tool icon to which 
you want to add tabs. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. Select  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Input/Output Tabs #!EF in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Edit #!EF pull-down menu and 
select  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Add Input Tab #!EF in the cascade menu. An 
input tab is added to the icon. #!N #!I30 #!N 3. 
Repeat Step 2 as many times as necessary. #!N #!I0 #!N 
#!EF #!N Note: You can also remove tabs from a tool 
icon by following the same procedure, but select  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Remove Input 
Tab #!EF in Step 2. #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic 
#!EF #!N #!N  #!Ltscdps,dxall59 h Connecting Scattered Data Points  #!EL  #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   #!N 
